What you need to know:  KCB reckon that Kabras, who are the reigning champions, are now a different outfit from yesteryears and will pose all sorts of problems to them at Kakamege ASK Showground in Saturday’s finalKCB team manager, former 15s and sevens international Philip Wamae said Thursday that Kabras Sugar had transformed to an 80 minutes sideWamae noted that Kabras had exhibited sound tactical and technical play this season, boasting the best defence in the league that has conceded a tournament low 77 points compared to KCB’s 117